BY BAMIDELE FAMOOFO Fidson Healthcare Plc, a leading pharmaceutical manufacturing company in Nigeria has declared a double reward for its shareholders for the financial year ended December 31, 2021. A final dividend of 50 kobo per 50 kobo ordinary share is payable to shareholders whose names appear in the register of members as at the close of business on 8th July, 2022. A bonus issue of one new share for existing 10 shares will also be paid to shareholders. On July 29, 2022, dividends will be paid electronically to shareholders whose names appear on the Register of Members as at 8th July, 2022, and who have completed the e-dividend registration and mandated the Registrar to pay their dividends directly into their Bank accounts. The register of shareholders will be closed from 11th July, 2022 to 15th July, 2022 both days inclusive. Qualification date is 8th July, 2022. Meanwhile, shareholders with dividend warrants and share certificates that have remained unclaimed, or are yet to be presented for payment or returned for validation are advised to complete the e-dividend registration or contact the registrar. The Companyâ€™s Annual General Meeting will be held on 28th July, 2022.